name: Medicine Ball Supine Chest Throw
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a bench with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the medicine ball with both hands, extending your arms straight up above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the medicine ball towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Explosively push the medicine ball upwards, extending your arms fully and throwing the ball as high as possible. | Step:5 Catch the medicine ball and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Extension Incline Bench Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and attach a cable machine to the low pulley. | Step:2 Attach a rope handle to the cable machine and sit on the incline bench facing the machine. | Step:3 Grab the rope handle with an overhand grip and lean forward, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, pulling the rope towards your upper chest while keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing Close-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight in front of you, gripping the bar or handles with a close grip. | Step:4 Pull the bar or handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Delt Row (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Keep your elbows slightly bent and pull the rope towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Step Up Single Leg Balance With Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a step or platform with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Engage your core and push through your right heel to lift your body up onto the step, bringing your left knee up towards your chest. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, perform a bicep curl by bending your elbows and bringing the dumbbells towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells back down and simultaneously lower your left foot back to the ground. | Step:6 Repeat the movement on the opposite side, stepping up with your left foot and curling the dumbbells. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Let the dumbbell hang at arm's length in front of your thighs, with your palm facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, exhale and lift the dumbbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Wheel Run
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your hands on the wheel and your body straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and start rolling the wheel forward by extending your arms. | Step:3 Continue rolling until your body is fully extended and your arms are overhead. | Step:4 Reverse the movement by pulling the wheel back towards your body, using your core and arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upper Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your upper chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Wide-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with a wide overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from the hips. | Step:4 Pull the handle towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Upright Row (Back Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Let the dumbbells hang in front of your thighs, with your arms fully extended and your palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, exhale and lift the dumbbells straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Continue lifting until the dumbbells are at shoulder height, with your elbows pointing out to the sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Upright Row V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs, arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, exhale and lift the barbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Upright Row V. 3
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs, arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and back straight, exhale as you lift the barbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale as you slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Groin Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Side Crunch (Wall)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your back against a wall and your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:4 Engage your abs and lean to one side, bringing your elbow towards your hip. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Roller Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended straight above your head and your legs straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place the roller between your feet and grip it with your toes. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your legs off the ground and curl your knees towards your chest, rolling the roller towards your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position, rolling the roller away from your body. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips while keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing One Arm Row (With Towel)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a towel with one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Pull the towel towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the towel back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Place a dumbbell on the floor next to the bench. | Step:3 Stand facing the bench with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Bend at the waist and place your left knee and left hand on the bench for support. | Step:5 Pick up the dumbbell with your right hand using a reverse grip (palm facing down). | Step:6 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:7 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:8 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement. | Step:9 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. | Step:10 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:11 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with your left arm.

name: Weighted Kneeling Step With Swing
instructions: Step:1 Start in a kneeling position with your knees hip-width apart and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a weight in each hand, with your arms extended straight down in front of you. | Step:3 Engage your core and swing the weights up and overhead, keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Lower the weights back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Push With Run Release
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball at chest level. | Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and simultaneously push the medicine ball forward, extending your arms fully. | Step:3 As you push the ball forward, release it and let it roll forward. | Step:4 Quickly run forward and catch the ball before it hits the ground. | Step:5 Once you catch the ball, bring it back to your chest and repeat the movement with your left foot forward. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs and repeating the exercise for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Thibaudeau Kayak Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and sit facing the machine with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your right hand and extend your arm fully, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:3 Lean forward from your hips, keeping your back straight and your abs engaged. | Step:4 Pull the handle towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blade and bending your elbow, keeping your arm close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and perform with your left arm.

name: Crunch Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your shoulders off the ground, curling forward towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up a suspension trainer at an appropriate height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Lean back, keeping your body straight and your heels on the ground. | Step:5 Pull your chest towards the handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Posterior Step To Overhead Reach
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Take a step back with your right foot, landing on the ball of your foot. | Step:3 Bend your left knee and lower your body into a lunge position. | Step:4 As you lower into the lunge, simultaneously reach your arms overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the lunge, then return to the starting position by pushing through your left heel and bringing your right foot forward. | Step:6 Repeat the movement on the other side, stepping back with your left foot and bending your right knee. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pendlay Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Arm Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a barbell with one hand using an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your head in a neutral position. | Step:3 Pull the barbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Back And Forth Step
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Step forward with your right foot, bending your knee and lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Push off with your right foot and step back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat the movement with your left foot, alternating legs with each step. | Step:5 Continue stepping back and forth, maintaining a steady pace. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Stationary Bike Walk
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position on the stationary bike to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Place your feet on the pedals and secure them with the straps if available. | Step:3 Start pedaling at a comfortable pace, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:4 Maintain a steady rhythm and increase the resistance level if desired. | Step:5 Continue pedaling for the desired duration of your cardio workout. | Step:6 Cool down by gradually reducing your pace and resistance level. | Step:7 Stretch your leg muscles after the workout to prevent tightness and promote recovery.

name: Smith Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the smith machine. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the barbell up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated One Arm Alternate Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench facing a cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with one hand and keep your arm fully extended in front of you. | Step:3 Pull the handle towards your body, retracting your shoulder blade and keeping your elbow close to your side. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:7 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Row (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the v-bar attachment with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the v-bar towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, keeping your back straight and your shoulders relaxed. | Step:3 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Twist Row (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a v-bar attachment to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Take a step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Pull the v-bar towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows. | Step:7 As you pull, twist your torso to one side, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:8 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, feeling the contraction in your upper back. | Step:9 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position, untwisting your torso. | Step:10 Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, alternating the twisting direction with each rep.

name: Band Kneeling Twisting Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Kneel down facing away from the anchor point and hold the band with both hands, keeping your elbows bent and close to your sides. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly twist your torso to one side, bringing your hands towards your opposite hip. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking On Incline Treadmill
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the incline level on the treadmill to your desired intensity. | Step:2 Stand on the treadmill with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Start walking at a comfortable pace, ensuring that you maintain proper form. | Step:4 Engage your core muscles and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Continue walking on the incline treadmill for the desired duration of your cardio workout. | Step:6 Gradually decrease the incline and speed of the treadmill to cool down before stopping.

name: Dumbbell Step-Up Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a step or platform with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your sides. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the step, ensuring your entire foot is on the surface. | Step:3 Push through your right heel and lift your body up onto the step, bringing your left foot up as well. | Step:4 Once both feet are on the step, lower your left foot back down to the starting position, keeping your right foot on the step. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, alternating which foot you step up with each time. | Step:6 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rear Delt Row (Stirrups)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a stirrup handle to a low cable pulley and stand facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with your left hand and take a step back with your right foot, positioning your body at a slight angle. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 With your left arm extended and your palm facing down, pull the handle towards your chest by retracting your shoulder blade. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your shoulder blade. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:7 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with your right arm.

name: Bodyweight Squatting Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding onto a sturdy object or suspension trainer with your arms extended. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and your knees behind your toes. | Step:3 From the squat position, pull your body up towards the object or suspension trainer, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Squat Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the band handles with your palms facing each other and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:4 Bend your knees and lower into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest lifted. | Step:5 From the squat position, pull the band handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to waist level. | Step:2 Stand facing the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with one hand using an overhand grip, with your palm facing down. | Step:5 Keep your elbow close to your body and pull the bar towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Inverted Row V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height on a Smith machine or use a suspension trainer. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar or suspension trainer and grab it with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Walk your feet forward, leaning back until your body is at a slight angle. | Step:4 Keep your body straight and pull your chest up towards the bar or handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever T Bar Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footplate position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your torso, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Palm Rotational Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Let your arms hang straight down, palms facing your body. | Step:4 Engage your core and pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 As you pull the dumbbells up, rotate your palms so they face away from your body. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, rotating your palms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a high pulley and stand facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Hold the handle with both hands and place it behind your head, keeping your elbows bent. | Step:3 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Keeping your abs engaged, exhale and crunch your torso down towards your knees, bringing your elbows towards your thighs. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse T-Bar Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footplate position on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Let the dumbbells hang in front of your thighs, with your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, exhale and lift the dumbbells straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a bench or step with a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Place one foot on the bench or step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Push through your heel and step up onto the bench or step, fully extending your hip and knee. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the top, then lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the opposite leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hands Bike
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and handlebar position to a comfortable level. | Step:2 Sit on the ergometer with your back straight and feet on the pedals. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with your hands and position your arms at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Start pedaling with your hands, pushing and pulling the handles in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Continue pedaling for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Lever High Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and foot platform to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the foot platform. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Knee Touch Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your shoulder blades off the ground and reach your right hand towards your left knee. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat, this time reaching your left hand towards your right knee. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated High Row (V-Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the v-bar attachment with an overhand grip, palms facing each other, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from the hips. | Step:4 Pull the v-bar towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Side Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and stand sideways to the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with the hand furthest from the machine and place your other hand on your hip. | Step:3 Keep your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 With your abs engaged, bend sideways at the waist, bringing your elbow down towards your hip. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Stability Ball Crunch (Full Range Hands Behind Head)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly curl your upper body forward, bringing your chest towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing Close-Grip One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a dumbbell in one hand with a neutral grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Floor Seated Wide-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended and your back straight. | Step:2 Attach a cable handle to a low pulley and position the cable machine behind you. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with a wide overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your chest lifted. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (On Stability Ball, Arms Straight)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie back on the ball until your lower back is supported and your upper body is parallel to the floor. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:4 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the ball, curling your shoulders towards your hips. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever One Arm Lateral High Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handle with one hand and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Pull the handle towards your body, keeping your elbow close to your side. | Step:4 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your upper body towards your knees, curling your torso. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverted Row On Bench
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bench at a height that allows your body to hang freely underneath it. | Step:2 Lie face up on the ground with your head towards the bench. | Step:3 Reach up and grab the bench with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Position your body so that your heels are on the ground and your arms are fully extended. | Step:5 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull your chest up towards the bench. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Grip Row (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Let your arms hang straight down, fully extended, with a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Rear Delt Row (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable attachment with both hands, palms facing each other, and step back to create tension in the cable. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the cable back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Low Seated Row Controlled
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. Maintain controlled form throughout. | Step:4 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kneeling Crunch - Gentle Variation
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a high pulley and kneel down facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Hold the rope handle with both hands and place it behind your head, keeping your elbows out to the sides. | Step:3 Keeping your hips stationary, flex your waist and crunch your torso down towards your thighs. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. Maintain gentle form throughout. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Cable High Row (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Kneel down in front of the cable machine and grab the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit back on your heels, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the bar towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain side form throughout.

name: Blunt Cable Standing Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable handle to a high pulley and stand facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Hold the handle with both hands and place it behind your head, keeping your elbows bent. | Step:3 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Keeping your abs engaged, exhale and crunch your torso down towards your knees, bringing your elbows towards your thighs. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. Emphasize blunt control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kneeling Rear Delt Row (With Rope) (Male) Expanded
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low cable pulley and kneel down facing the machine. | Step:2 (expanded variation) Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and extend your arms fully in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, pull the rope towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades. | Step:4 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement and hold for a brief pause. | Step:5 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Intense Kettlebell Two Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a kettlebell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Pull the kettlebells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain intense form throughout.

name: Precision Style Lever Bent-Over Row With V-Bar
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Pull the v-bar towards your abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the weight back to the starting position. Emphasize precision control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Narrow Style Band Jack Knife Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engage your abs and lift your legs and upper body simultaneously, bringing your hands towards your feet. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on narrow movement.

name: Single Style Cable Standing Crunch (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Focus on single movement. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands and bring it behind your head, keeping your elbows bent. | Step:4 Engage your abs and slowly crunch your torso forward, bringing your elbows towards your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the crunch, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Core Barbell Upright Row V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs, arms fully extended. Perform with core intensity. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, exhale and lift the barbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Step Up Single Leg Balance With Bicep Curl - Chair Variation
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a step or platform with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Engage your core and push through your right heel to lift your body up onto the step, bringing your left knee up towards your chest. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, perform a bicep curl by bending your elbows and bringing the dumbbells towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells back down and simultaneously lower your left foot back to the ground. | Step:6 (chair variation) Repeat the movement on the opposite side, stepping up with your left foot and curling the dumbbells. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Standing Low Row - Lateral Variation
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a stable anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the band with one hand, palm facing inward, and step back to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pull the band towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the band back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides. Emphasize lateral control.

name: Pulse Style Walk Elliptical Cross Trainer
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the resistance level and incline of the elliptical machine to your desired settings. | Step:2 Step onto the pedals of the machine and grip the handles lightly. | Step:3 Begin by pushing down with your feet and pulling the handles towards your body. | Step:4 Continue this motion, alternating between pushing and pulling, to simulate a walking or running motion. | Step:5 Maintain a steady pace and keep your core engaged throughout the exercise. Emphasize pulse control. | Step:6 Continue for the desired duration of your cardio workout. | Step:7 Gradually decrease the intensity and speed of the machine before stepping off.

name: Cable Incline Bench Row - Elite Variation
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and attach a cable handle to the low pulley. | Step:2 Sit on the bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip and extend your arms fully in front of you. Perform with elite intensity. | Step:4 Lean forward from your hips while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the cable handle towards your chest by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pointed Cable Palm Rotational Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Step back to create tension on the cable, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent. Emphasize pointed control. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your palms to face upwards as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stability Lever Narrow Grip Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to ensure proper form. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a narrow grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your torso, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. Focus on stability movement. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith One Arm Row Linear
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to waist level. | Step:2 Stand facing the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. Emphasize linear control. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with one hand using an overhand grip, with your palm facing down. | Step:5 Keep your elbow close to your body and pull the bar towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Seated Row With Reverse
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, keeping your back straight and your shoulders relaxed. | Step:3 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Focus on reverse movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walk Elliptical Cross Trainer - Expanded Variation
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the resistance level and incline of the elliptical machine to your desired settings. | Step:2 Step onto the pedals of the machine and grip the handles lightly. | Step:3 Begin by pushing down with your feet and pulling the handles towards your body. | Step:4 Continue this motion, alternating between pushing and pulling, to simulate a walking or running motion. Emphasize expanded control. | Step:5 Maintain a steady pace and keep your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Continue for the desired duration of your cardio workout. | Step:7 Gradually decrease the intensity and speed of the machine before stepping off.

name: Smith Bent Over Row With Declined
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Perform with declined intensity. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Grip Row (Female) Hold
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing your body. Perform with hold intensity. | Step:3 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Let your arms hang straight down, fully extended, with a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Narrow Grip Seated Row - Strength Variation
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to ensure proper form. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a narrow grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your torso, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement. Maintain strength form throughout. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Fluid Dumbbell Step-Up Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a step or platform with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your sides. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the step, ensuring your entire foot is on the surface. | Step:3 Push through your right heel and lift your body up onto the step, bringing your left foot up as well. | Step:4 (fluid variation) Once both feet are on the step, lower your left foot back down to the starting position, keeping your right foot on the step. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, alternating which foot you step up with each time. | Step:6 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Extended Style Inverted Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height or use a suspension trainer. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar or suspension trainer, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grab the bar or handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back, keeping your body straight and your heels on the ground. | Step:5 Pull your chest towards the bar or handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Perform with extended intensity.

name: Cross Body Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground and twist to bring your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps Narrow Pull-Ups
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull yourself up towards the bar, focusing on using your biceps to lift your body. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Oblique Crunches Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your shoulder blades off the floor, rotating your torso to one side. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then lower your shoulder blades back down to the floor. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, alternating sides with each repetition.

name: Dumbbell Step-Up Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a bench or step with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the bench or step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Step up onto the bench or step with your right foot, pushing through your heel to lift your body up. | Step:4 As you step up, simultaneously lift your left knee towards your chest. | Step:5 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your left foot back to the ground while keeping your right foot on the bench or step. | Step:6 Repeat the movement with your left foot on the bench or step. | Step:7 Continue alternating between your right and left foot for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline Seated Wide-Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the decline bench facing the cable machine with your feet securely placed on the footrests. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with a wide overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the cable back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walk Elliptical Cross Trainer
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the resistance level and incline of the elliptical machine to your desired settings. | Step:2 Step onto the pedals of the machine and grip the handles lightly. | Step:3 Begin by pushing down with your feet and pulling the handles towards your body. | Step:4 Continue this motion, alternating between pushing and pulling, to simulate a walking or running motion. | Step:5 Maintain a steady pace and keep your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Continue for the desired duration of your cardio workout. | Step:7 Gradually decrease the intensity and speed of the machine before stepping off.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Pull the kettlebell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat with the other arm.

name: Cable High Row (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Kneel down in front of the cable machine and grab the bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit back on your heels, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the bar towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the bar back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Narrow Stance Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you slowly lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Bent-Over Row With V-Bar
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the v-bar with an overhand grip, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Pull the v-bar towards your abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the weight back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Negative Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with one hand, palm facing inward, and extend your arm fully. | Step:4 Pull the cable handle towards your body, keeping your elbow close to your side, until your hand reaches your lower chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly extend your arm back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Inverted Row With Straps
instructions: Step:1 Set up a suspension trainer or straps at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point and grab the handles with an overhand grip. | Step:3 Walk your feet forward, leaning back until your body is at an angle. | Step:4 Keep your body straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull your chest towards the handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet on the footrests. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Crunch (Chest Pad)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and chest pad position according to your comfort. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the chest pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or side bars for stability. | Step:4 Engage your abs and slowly lean back, allowing the chest pad to move with you. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the maximum contraction, feeling the tension in your abs. | Step:6 Slowly return to the starting position by contracting your abs and pulling yourself back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Oblique Crunch V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your shoulder blades off the ground, rotating your torso to one side. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then lower your shoulder blades back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Frog Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Incline Bench Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and attach a cable handle to the low pulley. | Step:2 Sit on the bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip and extend your arms fully in front of you. | Step:4 Lean forward from your hips while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the cable handle towards your chest by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows. | Step:6 Squeeze your back muscles at the top of the movement, then slowly extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Narrow Grip Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to ensure proper form. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a narrow grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your torso, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handles and return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Straight Back Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended and loop the resistance band around your feet. | Step:2 Hold the ends of the resistance band with your hands, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back, engaging your core. | Step:4 Pull the resistance band towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Side Bend Crunch (Bosu Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a cable handle in one hand. | Step:2 Place the other hand on your hip. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly bend sideways towards the hand holding the cable, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row_Shoulder
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:3 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight down towards the floor, with a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Raise the dumbbells out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Crunch (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands and bring it behind your head, keeping your elbows bent. | Step:4 Engage your abs and slowly crunch your torso forward, bringing your elbows towards your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the crunch, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Bar Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, until your torso is almost parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pull the ez barbell towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the ez barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Twisting Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold the band with one hand and extend your arm fully in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, pull the band towards your body by bending your elbow and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 At the same time, twist your torso towards the side of the pulling arm. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension in the band and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Rope Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the rowing machine with your feet flat on the footrests and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable ropes with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pull the cable ropes towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Squat Row (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, with your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and pull the rope towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Keep your elbows close to your body and continue pulling until your hands reach your chest. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the rope and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Back Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the cable row machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from the hips. | Step:4 Pull the cable handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a bench or step with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Place your right foot on the bench or step, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. | Step:3 Push through your right heel and lift your body up onto the bench or step, straightening your right leg. | Step:4 Bring your left foot up onto the bench or step, standing fully upright. | Step:5 Step back down with your left foot, followed by your right foot, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Cable Squat Row (With Rope Attachment) Heavy
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 (heavy variation) Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, with your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and pull the rope towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Keep your elbows close to your body and continue pulling until your hands reach your chest. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the rope and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Standing Twisting Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your upper back, crossing it in front of your chest. | Step:2 Hold the ends of the band with your hands, keeping your elbows bent and close to your sides. | Step:3 Engage your abs and twist your torso to one side, bringing your elbow towards the opposite knee. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Straight Back High Row (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Kneel down facing the cable machine and grab the handle with one hand. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the handle towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other arm.

name: Cable Kneeling Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a high pulley and kneel down facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Hold the rope handle with both hands and place it behind your head, keeping your elbows out to the sides. | Step:3 Keeping your hips stationary, flex your waist and crunch your torso down towards your thighs. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Short Stride Run
instructions: Step:1 Find an open space or a treadmill to perform the exercise. | Step:2 Stand tall with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:3 Start jogging in place, lifting your knees high and pumping your arms. | Step:4 After a few seconds, start taking short strides forward, maintaining a quick pace. | Step:5 Continue running with short strides for the desired duration or distance.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a kettlebell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Pull one kettlebell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position and repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the bar at hip height. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Pull the bar towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the bar back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing One Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Let the dumbbell hang straight down in front of you, with your arm fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: One Arm Towel Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a towel with one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Extend your arm fully, allowing the towel to hang in front of you. | Step:4 Pull the towel towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the towel back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Ski Step
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Jump to the right, landing on your right foot while swinging your left leg behind your right leg. | Step:4 Immediately jump to the left, landing on your left foot while swinging your right leg behind your left leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating jumps from side to side, mimicking a skiing motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight down towards the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:3 Engaging your back muscles, lift the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever One Arm Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your head up. | Step:3 Let the barbell hang in front of you with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the barbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse-Grip Straight Back Seated High Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the seat facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the cable attachment with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward from your hips. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your torso by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the contraction, then slowly release the cable back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Overhead Crunch (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a weight plate or dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms overhead. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly curl your torso forward, bringing your chest towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your torso back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Air Bike
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your hands placed behind your head. | Step:2 Lift your legs off the ground and bend your knees at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Bring your right elbow towards your left knee while simultaneously straightening your right leg. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement on the opposite side, bringing your left elbow towards your right knee while straightening your left leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides in a pedaling motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Run (Equipment)
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing upright with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your upper body relaxed. | Step:3 Begin jogging in place, lifting your knees up towards your chest and landing softly on the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Maintain a steady pace and continue jogging for the desired duration or distance. | Step:5 Remember to breathe deeply and maintain good posture throughout the exercise.

name: Band Bicycle Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your hands behind your head and your knees bent. | Step:2 Lift your feet off the ground and bring your right knee towards your chest while simultaneously twisting your torso to bring your left elbow towards your right knee. | Step:3 Straighten your right leg while bringing your left knee towards your chest and twisting your torso to bring your right elbow towards your left knee. | Step:4 Continue alternating the twisting motion, as if you are pedaling a bicycle, while keeping your core engaged throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Palm Rotational Row
