instructions: Step:1 Attach a handle to a cable machine at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Step back to create tension on the cable, keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Pull the handle towards your body, rotating your palms to face upwards as you do so. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Grab a dumbbell in each hand and sit on the bench with your chest against the incline. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, allowing the dumbbells to hang straight down from your shoulders. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold the cable attachment with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Pull the cable attachment straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Slowly lower the cable attachment back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squat Jump Step Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Explode upwards, jumping off the ground as high as you can. | Step:4 Land softly on your feet and immediately step back with one leg into a reverse lunge. | Step:5 Lower your body down until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:6 Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat the jump and lunge sequence on the other leg. | Step:8 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable to a low pulley and lie down facing up on a mat. | Step:2 Hold the cable with both hands and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lift your legs up, bringing your thighs towards your chest. | Step:4 While keeping your upper body stable, curl your pelvis up towards your chest, lifting your hips off the mat. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide-Grip Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs, arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, exhale and lift the barbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Low Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly forward, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Two Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a kettlebell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Pull the kettlebells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Squatting Row (With Towel)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a towel in front of you with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:3 As you lower into the squat, simultaneously pull the towel towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then slowly return to the starting position while extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Standing Low Row
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a stable anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the band with one hand, palm facing inward, and step back to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pull the band towards your waist, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the band back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Run
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing upright with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your upper body relaxed. | Step:3 Begin jogging in place, lifting your knees up towards your chest and landing softly on the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Maintain a steady pace and continue jogging for the desired duration or distance. | Step:5 Remember to breathe deeply and maintain good posture throughout the exercise.

name: Cable Tuck Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach a cable to a low pulley and lie down on a mat facing up. | Step:2 Hold the cable with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your chest. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lift your legs up, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 At the same time, curl your pelvis up towards your chest, lifting your hips off the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Lying Leg Raise With Throw Down
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Raise your legs until they are perpendicular to the ground. | Step:5 Lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Simultaneously, throw your legs down towards the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:7 Raise your legs back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stationary Bike Run
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Place your feet on the pedals and secure them with the straps if available. | Step:3 Start pedaling at a comfortable pace. | Step:4 Maintain a steady rhythm and increase the resistance as desired. | Step:5 Engage your core muscles to maintain stability and proper posture. | Step:6 Continue pedaling for the desired duration of your workout. | Step:7 Gradually decrease the resistance and slow down before coming to a complete stop. | Step:8 Stretch your legs and cool down after the workout.

name: Inverted Row Bent Knees
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height and lie underneath it. | Step:2 Grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Position your body so that your heels are on the ground and your body is straight. | Step:4 Pull your chest up towards the bar by squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench facing the backrest with your chest against it. | Step:3 Grab the barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing down) and hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the barbell towards your upper abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Narrow Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your chest up as you pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Standing Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the band with both hands and bring it up to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body. | Step:4 Engage your abs and slowly crunch forward, bringing your chest towards your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the crunch, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a cable machine with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and position it behind your head. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly curl your upper body forward, bringing your chest towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Deadlift With Stepbox Support
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Place your left foot on a stepbox or elevated surface behind you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, hinge forward at the hips, lowering the dumbbell towards the ground. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbell, simultaneously lift your left leg behind you, maintaining a straight line from head to heel. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell until you feel a stretch in your right hamstring, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Step-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place a band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:2 Stand facing a step or platform with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:3 Step up onto the platform with your right foot, pushing through your heel. | Step:4 Extend your left leg behind you, keeping it straight. | Step:5 Lower your left foot back down to the ground. | Step:6 Repeat with your left foot stepping up onto the platform. | Step:7 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a weight plate or dumbbell on your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your shoulder blades are off the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Tuck Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your shoulder blades off the ground and bring your knees towards your chest, simultaneously curling your upper body towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your shoulder blades and extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Kneeling Rear Delt Row (With Rope) (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low cable pulley and kneel down facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the rope with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and extend your arms fully in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, pull the rope towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades. | Step:4 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement and hold for a brief pause. | Step:5 Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leverage machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handles or place your hands on the side pads for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly lean back, allowing the pad to move with you. | Step:4 Once your upper body is at a 45-degree angle, contract your abs and crunch forward, bringing your chest towards your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Vertical Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footplate position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:5 Pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Alternating Narrow Grip Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footplate position to ensure proper alignment. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back straight and feet flat on the footplate. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a narrow grip, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and shoulders back throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull one handle towards your torso while keeping the other handle stationary. | Step:6 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the end of the movement. | Step:7 Slowly return the handle to the starting position and repeat with the other side. | Step:8 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Bent-Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing your body. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Let the dumbbell hang straight down towards the floor, with your arm fully extended. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended along your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your feet off the ground, bringing your thighs perpendicular to the floor. | Step:3 Contract your abs and curl your hips off the floor, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Hanging Knee Raise With Throw Down
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest, keeping your legs together. | Step:3 Once your knees are at chest level, explosively throw your legs down towards the ground, extending them fully. | Step:4 Allow your legs to swing back up and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Crossover Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the rowing machine with your feet flat on the footrests and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the cable ropes with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the cable ropes towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Elevated Seated Row
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the elevated seat facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Grab the cable rope handles with an overhand grip, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and lean slightly back, maintaining a slight bend in your knees. | Step:4 Pull the cable towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your back muscles. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully contracted position. | Step:6 Slowly release the tension and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Lying Leg Raise With Lateral Throw Down
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Place your hands under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:4 While keeping your legs together, lower them to one side until they are a few inches above the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then lift your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the movement to the other side. | Step:7 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Renegade Row
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands gripping the kettlebells and your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Pull one kettlebell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position and repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Standing Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band under your feet. | Step:2 Hold the band handles with your palms facing each other and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the band towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Unilateral Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself facing the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Pull the handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Narrow Push-Up On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and position yourself in a push-up position with your hands on the ball, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ball by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever T-Bar Reverse Grip Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:4 Pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (Hands Overhead)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight above your head. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Crunch (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie back on the ball until your lower back is supported and your upper body is parallel to the floor. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:4 Engage your abs and lift your upper body towards your knees, curling your torso forward. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cambered Bar Lying Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up a barbell on the floor and lie face down on a bench with your chest just off the edge. | Step:2 Reach down and grab the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 With your legs straight and feet on the ground, lift the barbell off the floor by extending your arms. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your core engaged as you pull the handles towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Runners Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your left foot planted. | Step:3 Bend your right knee and lower your body down, keeping your left leg straight. | Step:4 Place your hands on your right thigh for support. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Lever Seated Crunch V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leverage machine with your back against the pad and your feet secured under the footpads. | Step:2 Place your hands on the handles or the sides of the seat for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly crunch forward, bringing your chest towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your abs. | Step:5 Slowly return to the starting position, allowing your back to round slightly. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Leg Raise Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the leverage machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the footrests. | Step:2 Grasp the handles or sidebars for stability. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly raise your legs up towards your chest, curling your torso forward at the same time. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and torso back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Let your arms hang straight down towards the floor, with your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rear Delt Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp a bar or handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:4 Pull the bar or handles towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly release and extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverted Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up a bar at waist height or use a suspension trainer. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar or suspension trainer, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grab the bar or handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Lean back, keeping your body straight and your heels on the ground. | Step:5 Pull your chest towards the bar or handles, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower yourself back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Walking On Stepmill
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the stepmill machine to a comfortable level. | Step:2 Step onto the machine and place your hands on the handrails for support. | Step:3 Start walking by placing one foot on a step and then the other, alternating between legs. | Step:4 Maintain an upright posture and engage your core muscles. | Step:5 Continue walking for the desired duration or distance. | Step:6 Gradually increase the intensity or speed as you become more comfortable with the exercise. | Step:7 Remember to cool down and stretch after completing the exercise.

name: Medicine Ball Catch And Overhead Throw
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball in both hands at chest level. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Lower your body into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Explosively extend your hips and legs, while simultaneously throwing the medicine ball overhead. | Step:5 Release the ball at the top of the movement and catch it on the way down. | Step:6 Lower your body back into the squat position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push To Run
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:3 Push through your hands to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Quickly bring one knee towards your chest, then quickly switch and bring the other knee towards your chest. | Step:5 Continue alternating knees as fast as you can while maintaining good form. | Step:6 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Reverse Crunch
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your knees up towards your chest, curling your pelvis towards your ribcage. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your knees back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Standing Row (With Towel)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a towel in front of you with both hands. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Pull the towel towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Two Arm Row
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your chest against the backrest and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip. | Step:4 Lean forward and let your arms hang straight down, fully extended. | Step:5 Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chin-Ups (Narrow Parallel Grip)
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with a narrow parallel grip, palms facing towards you. | Step:2 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Upright Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs, arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and core engaged, exhale and lift the barbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Bent Over Row
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, until your torso is almost parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pull the barbell towards your lower chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or have someone hold your feet down. | Step:2 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:4 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Battling Ropes
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold one end of the rope in each hand, with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Raise your arms to shoulder height, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Begin making alternating waves with the ropes by rapidly raising and lowering each arm. | Step:5 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Triceps Dip (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height. | Step:2 Kneel down on the pad facing the machine, with your hands gripping the handles. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and close to the machine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Alternating V-Up With Simple
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engage your abs and lift your legs and upper body off the ground simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 As you lower your legs and upper body back down, switch the position of your legs, crossing one over the other. Focus on simple movement. | Step:4 Repeat the movement, alternating the position of your legs with each repetition. | Step:5 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse Calf Raises
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine bar to a height just below your shoulders. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet hip-width apart and toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Place the balls of your feet on the edge of a step or platform, with your heels hanging off. | Step:4 Hold onto the bar for support, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:5 Raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Front Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band in front of your thighs with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and lift the band up in front of you until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the band back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reclining Big Toe Pose With Rope
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Loop the rope around the ball of your right foot and hold the ends of the rope with your hands. | Step:3 Slowly raise your right leg towards your chest, keeping your knee straight and your foot flexed. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Y-Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band in front of your thighs with your palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and lift them up and out to the sides, forming a 'Y' shape with your body. | Step:3 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Push Single Response
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the medicine ball at chest level. | Step:2 Extend your arms forward, pushing the medicine ball away from your chest. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the medicine ball back to your chest. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and keep your arms straight. | Step:3 Exhale and raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Triceps Dip On High Parallel Bars
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your hands gripping the bars and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Drop Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Once your chest is just above the ground, explosively push yourself up, lifting your hands off the ground. | Step:4 As you push up, quickly move your hands out to the sides and slightly forward, allowing your body to drop down towards the ground. | Step:5 Catch yourself with your hands in the wider position and immediately lower your chest towards the ground again. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up motion, dropping down and catching yourself with your hands in the narrower position. | Step:7 Continue alternating between the wider and narrower hand positions for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly (Parallel Grip)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a parallel grip, palms facing each other, and keep your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Exhale and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the handles back and outward, away from your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place a band around your upper arms, just above the elbows. | Step:2 Assume a push-up position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: London Bridge
instructions: Step:1 Attach the rope to a high anchor point. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the rope towards your body, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the peak of the movement, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Otis Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Muscle Up (On Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and pull your chest towards the bar, keeping your body straight. | Step:4 Once your chest reaches the bar, push down with your hands and drive your elbows back, lifting your body above the bar. | Step:5 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your height and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place your shoulders under the pads and hold onto the handles for stability. | Step:3 Raise your heels as high as possible by extending your ankles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up Medicine Ball
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands on the medicine ball, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Push From 3 Point Stance
instructions: Step:1 Start in a 3 point stance with one hand on the medicine ball and the other hand on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your legs and position your body in a straight line. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Push the medicine ball away from your body, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Seated One Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the footrest. | Step:2 Place one leg on the footrest and keep the other leg off the footrest. | Step:3 Using your calf muscles, raise your heel as high as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Fierce Weighted Straight Bar Dip
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 (fierce variation) Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Alternating V-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engage your abs and lift your legs and upper body off the ground simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 As you lower your legs and upper body back down, switch the position of your legs, crossing one over the other. | Step:4 Repeat the movement, alternating the position of your legs with each repetition. | Step:5 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Supine Style Band Alternating V-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engage your abs and lift your legs and upper body off the ground simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 As you lower your legs and upper body back down, switch the position of your legs, crossing one over the other. Focus on supine movement. | Step:4 Repeat the movement, alternating the position of your legs with each repetition. | Step:5 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Wide-Grip Chest Dip (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired height and secure your knees on the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a wide grip and keep your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Assisted Chin-Up With Twisted
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the leverage machine to your desired resistance level. | Step:2 Stand on the foot platform and grip the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended, keeping your body straight. | Step:4 (twisted variation) Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the handles, leading with your chest. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the handles. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a stationary object at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band with both hands in front of you. | Step:3 Keep your arms straight and lift them out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. | Step:5 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your knees are at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the footrests. | Step:3 Place your hands on the side handles for stability. | Step:4 Engage your abductors and slowly push your legs apart, away from the midline of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring your legs back together to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Rotary Calf
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your knees are slightly bent and your feet are flat on the footplate. | Step:2 Place your toes on the footplate, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Push through the balls of your feet, raising your heels as high as possible. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Athletic Style Battling Ropes
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold one end of the rope in each hand, with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Raise your arms to shoulder height, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 (athletic variation) Begin making alternating waves with the ropes by rapidly raising and lowering each arm. | Step:5 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your knees are slightly bent and your feet are flat on the footplate. | Step:2 Place your toes on the footplate with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push through the balls of your feet to raise your heels as high as possible. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Seated Twist Pure
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you and your back straight. | Step:2 Wrap the band around your waist and hold the ends with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly twist your torso to one side, keeping your back straight and your feet on the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 (pure variation) Repeat the twist to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Standing Chin-Up With Focused
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired assistance level. | Step:2 (focused variation) Stand on the foot platform and grip the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and shoulders back, engage your core, and slightly bend your knees. | Step:4 Pull your body up by flexing your elbows and driving your elbows down towards your sides. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Prone Medicine Ball Close Grip Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands on the medicine ball, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Push back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain prone form throughout.

name: Weighted Round Arm
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Continue lifting your arms until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hack Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable weight. | Step:2 Stand on the sled machine with your toes on the platform and your heels hanging off. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles for stability. | Step:4 Raise your heels as high as possible by pushing through the balls of your feet. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Front Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on the floor. | Step:2 Place your forearms on the ground, with your elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:3 Extend your legs straight out behind you, with your toes on the ground. | Step:4 Engage your core and lift your body off the ground, balancing on your forearms and toes. | Step:5 Keep your body in a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:6 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:7 Lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Hanging Knee Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core muscles and lift your knees towards your chest, bending at the hips and knees. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your abs. | Step:4 Slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Shoulder Raises
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to an incline position. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:5 Raise the barbell up towards the ceiling, leading with your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flexible Assisted Prone Hamstring
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat or bench with your legs fully extended. | Step:2 (flexible variation) Have a partner or use a resistance band to secure your ankles. | Step:3 Engage your hamstrings and lift your legs towards your glutes, keeping your knees straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rough Band Hip Lift
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place a resistance band just above your knees. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:4 Press your heels into the ground and lift your hips off the floor, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Focus on rough movement.

name: Fast Style Resistance Band Seated Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Wrap the resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:3 Place your hands on the sides of the chair or bench for support. | Step:4 (fast variation) Engage your abductors (outer thigh muscles) and slowly push your knees apart, against the resistance of the band. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring your knees back together. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rough Band Push Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band securely to a stable anchor point. | Step:2 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold the band with both hands and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. Focus on rough movement. | Step:4 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Lying Hip Internal Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs straight and a resistance band looped around your feet. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring them towards your chest, keeping your feet together. | Step:3 Slowly rotate your knees outwards, away from each other, while keeping your feet together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Russian Twist V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Hold the weight with both hands in front of your chest. | Step:3 Lean back slightly to engage your core muscles. | Step:4 Twist your torso to the right, bringing the weight towards the right side of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the weight towards the left side of your body. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Chest Dip (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired height and secure your knees on the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Lunge With Swing Twisted
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, swing the weights forward and upward, keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and return to the starting position, swinging the weights back down. | Step:5 (twisted variation) Repeat with your left foot and continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band V-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engaging your abs, lift your legs and upper body off the ground simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Gripper Hands
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and grip the handles of the leverage machine. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Exhale and squeeze the handles, contracting your forearms. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly release and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Hip Lift
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place a resistance band just above your knees. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:4 Press your heels into the ground and lift your hips off the floor, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Motion Russian Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Hold the medicine ball with both hands in front of your chest. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, engaging your abs and keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Slowly twist your torso to the right, bringing the medicine ball towards the right side of your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the medicine ball towards the left side of your body. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Seated Hip Internal Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place a resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:3 Keep your knees bent at a 90-degree angle and your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and slowly rotate your knees outward, pushing against the resistance of the band. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Prone Hamstring
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat or bench with your legs fully extended. | Step:2 Have a partner or use a resistance band to secure your ankles. | Step:3 Engage your hamstrings and lift your legs towards your glutes, keeping your knees straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Muscle Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 As you reach the top of the movement, transition your grip so that your palms are facing towards you. | Step:4 Continue pulling yourself up until your chest reaches the bar, then pause for a moment. | Step:5 Slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Toe Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine bar to a height that allows you to comfortably stand with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Position yourself under the bar with your shoulders directly below it and your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Place the balls of your feet on a raised platform or weight plates, with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:4 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. | Step:6 Slowly raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body weight onto the balls of your feet. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Close Grip Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands on the medicine ball, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Push back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Reverse Calf Raises
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine bar to a height just below your shoulders. | Step:2 Stand facing the bar with your feet hip-width apart and toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Place the balls of your feet on the edge of a step or platform, with your heels hanging off. | Step:4 Hold onto the bar for support. | Step:5 Raise your heels as high as possible, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding the medicine ball at chest level. | Step:2 Extend your arms forward, pushing the medicine ball away from your chest with force. | Step:3 As you release the ball, follow through with your arms and torso, transferring your weight from your back foot to your front foot. | Step:4 Catch the ball as it rebounds off the wall or partner, and immediately repeat the movement. | Step:5 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rope Climb
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the rope with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grab the rope with both hands, palms facing towards you. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:4 Begin pulling yourself up the rope by alternating hand-over-hand movements. | Step:5 Use your legs to assist in the upward movement. | Step:6 Continue climbing until you reach the desired height or the top of the rope. | Step:7 To descend, reverse the hand-over-hand movement while controlling your descent. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Standing Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired assistance level. | Step:2 Stand on the foot platform and grip the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and shoulders back, engage your core, and slightly bend your knees. | Step:4 Pull your body up by flexing your elbows and driving your elbows down towards your sides. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Seated Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you and your back straight. | Step:2 Wrap the band around your waist and hold the ends with both hands. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly twist your torso to one side, keeping your back straight and your feet on the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the twist, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the twist to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Push Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band securely to a stable anchor point. | Step:2 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold the band with both hands and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Bench Dip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the smith machine with your back against the pad and your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the barbell, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then push through your heels to raise your hips off the ground. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:5 Hold for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and keep your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Exhale and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the handles back and outward, away from your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cycle Cross Trainer
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the cycle cross trainer. | Step:2 Place your feet on the pedals and grip the handlebars. | Step:3 Start pedaling in a smooth and controlled motion. | Step:4 Maintain a steady pace and increase the resistance if desired. | Step:5 Continue pedaling for the desired duration of your cardio workout.

name: Resistance Band Seated Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Wrap the resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:3 Place your hands on the sides of the chair or bench for support. | Step:4 Engage your abductors (outer thigh muscles) and slowly push your knees apart, against the resistance of the band. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring your knees back together. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Donkey Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the leverage machine to the appropriate height for your body. | Step:2 Position yourself facing the machine, with your toes on the foot platform and your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Place your hands on the handles or the support bars for stability. | Step:4 Engage your calves and lift your heels as high as possible, using the balls of your feet. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Forward Angled Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable weight and position yourself on the machine with your toes on the platform and your heels hanging off. | Step:2 Place your hands on the handles or the sides of the machine for support. | Step:3 Engage your calves and slowly raise your heels as high as possible, pushing against the resistance of the sled. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Hip Adduction
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Place your feet on the footrests and grasp the handles for stability. | Step:3 Engage your adductor muscles and slowly bring your legs together, squeezing your inner thighs. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Overhand Triceps Dip
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to the appropriate height and secure your body in position. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your body so that your arms are fully extended. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms close to your sides. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your elbows. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed. | Step:4 Lift your shoulders up towards your ears, squeezing your traps at the top. | Step:5 Hold for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Bent Knee Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to raise your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Russian Twist (Legs Up)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your knees bent and feet lifted off the ground, keeping your legs together. | Step:2 Hold the weight with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Lean back slightly to engage your core muscles. | Step:4 Twist your torso to the right, bringing the weight towards the ground on your right side. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the weight towards the ground on your left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your hips are slightly higher than your knees. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the footrests. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your back straight, slowly lean forward from your hips until your upper body is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position by pushing through your glutes and hamstrings. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Tire Flip
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the tire. | Step:2 Bend your knees and hinge at the hips, lowering into a squat position. | Step:3 Reach down and grab the bottom edge of the tire with both hands, fingers facing towards you. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and leg muscles, and explosively drive through your legs to lift the tire off the ground. | Step:5 As the tire flips over, use your upper body strength to guide it and maintain control. | Step:6 Once the tire is fully flipped, quickly step back and reset your stance. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Gripless Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with your palms facing inwards and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, exhale and elevate your shoulders as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a brief moment, then inhale and slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Lying Straight Leg Raise
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your feet together. | Step:2 Place the band around the arches of your feet and hold the ends of the band with your hands. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift both legs off the ground until they are perpendicular to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Hanging Leg-Hip Raise
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs up in front of you, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Continue lifting until your legs are parallel to the ground or slightly higher. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Lunge With Swing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, swing the weights forward and upward, keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and return to the starting position, swinging the weights back down. | Step:5 Repeat with your left foot and continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the band in front of your thighs with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and slowly raise them forward until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Standing Hand Squeeze
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a weight in each hand. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight in front of you, palms facing each other. | Step:3 Squeeze your hands together as hard as you can, engaging your forearms. | Step:4 Hold the squeeze for a few seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Decline Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a decline bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly lift your upper body off the bench, curling forward until your torso is perpendicular to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Hip Thrusts On Knees (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your feet flexed. | Step:2 Wrap the resistance band around your thighs, just above your knees. | Step:3 Place your hands on your hips or extend them out in front of you for balance. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and core muscles. | Step:5 Push your hips forward and squeeze your glutes as you lift your knees off the ground, extending your hips until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Hold the position for a moment, then slowly lower your knees back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Donkey Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand on a raised platform with your toes on the edge and your heels hanging off. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for support. | Step:3 Raise your heels as high as possible by extending your ankles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Two Legs Calf Raise - (Band Under Both Legs) V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place a resistance band under both feet. | Step:2 Hold the ends of the band with your hands for stability. | Step:3 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, using your calves. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith One Leg Floor Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the floor under the smith machine bar, facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Place the balls of your feet on a raised surface, such as a weight plate or block. | Step:3 Position the smith machine bar across your lower legs, just above your ankles. | Step:4 Hold onto the bar with your hands for stability. | Step:5 Raise your heels off the ground by extending your ankles, lifting your body up. | Step:6 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and keep your arms straight. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, lift your shoulders up towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Front Raise
