instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your thighs. | Step:2 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the dumbbells in front of you until they are at shoulder level. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Assisted Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the leverage machine to your desired resistance level. | Step:2 Stand on the foot platform and grip the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended, keeping your body straight. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the handles, leading with your chest. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the handles. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Kneeling Twist
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees resting on the pads and your upper body facing forward. | Step:2 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged, twist your torso to one side as far as comfortably possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the twist to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Dip
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your feet are flat on the ground and your knees are at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Grasp the handles of the leverage machine with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Russian Twist
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a weight or medicine ball with both hands in front of your chest. | Step:3 Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Slowly twist your torso to the right, bringing the weight or medicine ball towards the floor on your right side. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the weight or medicine ball towards the floor on your left side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Standing Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine bar to a height that allows you to stand with your feet flat on the ground and your shoulders under the bar. | Step:2 Position yourself under the bar with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Place your hands on the bar for stability. | Step:4 Engage your calves and slowly raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Gripless Shrug V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles or bars with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, lift your shoulders up towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sledge Hammer
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the sledge hammer with both hands. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Swing the sledge hammer down towards the ground, using your core and upper body strength. | Step:4 As you swing down, pivot your hips and transfer the force to the hammer. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Back Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your arms straight and allow the barbell to hang in front of your thighs. | Step:4 Lift your shoulders straight up towards your ears, squeezing your traps at the top. | Step:5 Hold for a moment, then lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hack One Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to an appropriate weight. | Step:2 Stand on the sled machine with one foot, keeping the other foot off the ground. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles for stability. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible, lifting your body up on the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:7 Switch legs and repeat the exercise.

name: Weighted Three Bench Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward, sliding your butt off the bench and supporting your weight with your arms. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a pronated grip and keep your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Exhale and push the handles forward, bringing them together in front of your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, squeezing your chest muscles. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly return to the starting position, allowing your chest muscles to stretch. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Close Grip Chin-Up On Dip Cage
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the dip cage and grab the parallel bars with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bars with your arms fully extended, feet off the ground, and body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bars, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bars, then pause for a moment. | Step:5 Slowly lower your body back down to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Tricep Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the front of the bench with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:3 Keep your back close to the bench and your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Straight Bar Dip
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Push Multiple Response
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball at chest level. | Step:2 Extend your arms forward, pushing the medicine ball away from your chest. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly bring the medicine ball back to your chest. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ski Ergometer
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and footrests to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:3 Sit up straight with your feet flat on the footrests. | Step:4 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Engage your triceps and push the handles down towards your thighs. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Jack Knife Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engage your abs and lift your legs and upper body simultaneously, bringing your hands towards your feet. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band under your feet, holding the ends with your hands. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and relaxed, and let the band hang in front of your thighs. | Step:3 Engage your traps by shrugging your shoulders upward, lifting the band as high as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower your shoulders back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
